<br>
The &quot;lower level&quot; pet focus items, shovel, torch, broom and stein do NOT increase your pet level.  They increase your pets HP/stats.  You get the same level of pets as without a focus item.  It does not increase your chance of summoning a higher level pet.  It has nothing to do with the level of your pet.  Nada.  Zilch.  Zero.<br>
<br>
The &quot;higher level&quot; pet focus items, the Staff of Elemental Mastery: Earth, water, air and fire, affect the level of the pet by one.<br>
<br>
My <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> personal</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> findings have been that the &quot;lower level&quot; focus items work for pets spells 4 to 49.  The &quot;higher level&quot; focus items work for pets spells 51 to 60.<br>
<br>
